cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically pedestrian detection, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel detection pipeline that benefits from the two-stage cascade strategy, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a simpler network architecture adapted for small input sizes, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed pipeline is also designed for real-time performance, which could place it under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
